name: A realtime collaborative writing game
description:
write.io (codename) is a collaborative writing game. You connect to the server (via browser, no install needed). The server then quickly matches you with a few fellow players to form a new writing group. All members of the writing group are online now, and start collaborating on writing a new story. The game works in rounds: in each round, players suggest different continuations to the current, ongoing story.

Every player sees in real time what every other player is writing, and can vote on his preferred continuation to the current plot. Once a particular continuation gets enough votes, it gets added to the ongoing story, and the round finishes (round often take around one minute). When a player suggests “The End” of the story, and his suggestions gets enough votes, the game and the story end.

The end result is a collaboratively created story.

sites_https_justification: The project website and repo use GitHub, which supports HTTPS using TLS. There's no separate download URL (use git to download from the repo).
contribution_justification: Non-trivial contribution file in repository: <https://github.com/tiny-dnn/tiny-dnn/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md>.
license_location_justification: Non-trivial license location file in repository: <https://github.com/tiny-dnn/tiny-dnn/blob/master/LICENSE>.
floss_license_justification: https://github.com/tiny-dnn/tiny-dnn/blob/master/LICENSE The BSD-3-Clause license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
floss_license_osi_justification: The BSD-3-Clause "Revised" license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI). The BSD-3-Clause license is approved by the Open Source Initiative (OSI).
documentation_basics_justification: Some documentation basics file contents found.
documentation_interface_justification: Interface about Layers (core building blocks in Neural Networks) is here: http://tiny-dnn.readthedocs.io/en/latest/layers/Layers.html Document of other APIs is: http://tiny-dnn.readthedocs.io/en/latest/how_tos/How-Tos.html
repo_public_justification: Repository on GitHub, which provides public git repositories with URLs.
repo_track_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git can track the changes, who made them, and when they were made.
repo_distributed_justification: Repository on GitHub, which uses git. git is distributed.
version_semver_justification: We are still in alpha release stage. We will follow the Semantic Versioning format from v1.0.0
release_notes_justification: We use Github release as release notes. See https://github.com/tiny-dnn/tiny-dnn/releases
build_floss_tools_justification: This project support both gcc and clang with CMake.
test_invocation_justification: The test suite uses gtest, and it is executable from command line.
tests_documented_added_justification: https://github.com/tiny-dnn/tiny-dnn/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md#making-changes says "Make sure you have added the necessary tests for your changes."
warnings_justification: We use -Wall -Wpedantic -Wno-narrowing flags for clang/gcc, and /W4 flag for MSVC. See https://github.com/tiny-dnn/tiny-dnn/blob/master/CMakeLists.txt
warnings_fixed_justification: We accepted pull requests addressing warnings. For example https://github.com/tiny-dnn/tiny-dnn/pull/506, https://github.com/tiny-dnn/tiny-dnn/pull/479 and https://github.com/tiny-dnn/tiny-dnn/pull/471.
warnings_strict_justification: We have made an effort to reduce warnings, but sometimes it is hard to be strict with them (especially for 3rd party libraries which we include in our code)
vulnerabilities_fixed_60_days_justificat: No such vulnerabilities at this time.
vulnerabilities_critical_fixed_justifica: No such vulnerabilities at this time.
dynamic_analysis_justification: Analyzed with Valgrind and Dr.memory by @nyanp etc.
dynamic_analysis_unsafe_justification: Analyzed with Valgrind and Dr.memory by @nyanp etc.
dynamic_analysis_enable_assertions_justi: We have runtime exceptions, and many external tests with assertions instead of run-time assertions.
dynamic_analysis_fixed_justification: No vulnerabilities found yet (so it is satisfied), and we have fixed some bugs discovered with dynamic code analysis.
test_continuous_integration_justificatio: The project uses Travis CI https://travis-ci.org/tiny-dnn/tiny-dnn and AppVeyor https://ci.appveyor.com/project/tinydnn/tiny-dnn.
discussion_justification: GitHub supports discussions on issues and pull requests. We also have the gitter disucussion rooms for developers https://gitter.im/tiny-dnn/developers and users https://gitter.im/tiny-dnn/users.
english_justification: All documentation is in English, and the project accepts bug reports and comments in English.
hardened_site_justification: Found all required security hardening headers.
build_reproducible_justification: This project is built automatically by Travis CI and AppVeyor.
